Sound Waves

Sound waves are mechanical waves that propagate through a medium such as air,
water, or solids. They cannot travel through a vacuum.

Properties
    Frequency: 20 Hz to 20 kHz (human hearing range)
    Speed: 343 m/s in air at 20°C
    Wavelength: Varies by frequency
    Wave Type: Mechanical, longitudinal wave

Applications
    Music, sonar, medical imaging, communication

